<h2>User Management Module</h2>
<p>This module allows a system administrator to manage (to enter or update) the user information.
    The admin can choose to create a new account or modify an existing account.<br><br><br></p>
<ol>
    <h4>Create a new account:</h4>
    <li>Select “Create an account” in home menu</li>
    <li>Enter a new username</li>
    <li>Enter password and re-enter to confirm password</li>
    <li>Enter first and last name of user</li>
    <li>Enter address, email, and phone number or user</li>
    <li>Enter class of the user. A user can be an administrator, doctor, radiologist, or a patient</li>
    <li>Enter the user's family doctor</li>
    <li>Press "Submit" to create account</li>
</ol>

<ol>
    <h4>Modify existing account:</h4>
    <li>Select “Update user information” in home menu</li>
    <li>Enter the username of the user</li>
    <li>Redirected to a form filled out with current account settings</li>
    <li>Change the desired fields</li>
    <li>Enter a new password and re-enter to confirm password</li>
    <li>Press “Submit” to modify account settings</li>
</ol>
